Title: Dune (Dune, #1)
Author: Frank Herbert
My Review: An absolute masterpiece of world-building. The scale is immense, the politics are intricate, and the themes are timeless. A must-read for any sci-fi fan.

Title: Dune Messiah (Dune, #2)
Author: Frank Herbert
My Review: A disappointing follow-up. The philosophical tone shift was jarring, and it lacked the grand adventure of the first book. Felt like a chore to finish.

Title: Guards! Guards! (Discworld, #8; City Watch, #1)
Author: Terry Pratchett
My Review: This is where I tell everyone to start with Discworld. The characters are hilarious and the satire is brilliant. Pure genius.

Title: The Left Hand of Darkness
Author: Ursula K. Le Guin
My Review: Groundbreaking exploration of gender and society. It's more than a sci-fi novel; it's a profound thought experiment.

Title: Babel, or the Necessity of Violence
Author: R.F. Kuang

Title: Piranesi
Author: Susanna Clarke
My Review: A beautiful, haunting mystery. The world is so unique and the atmosphere is incredible. I wish I could read it for the first time again.

Title: The Hobbit, or There and Back Again
Author: J.R.R. Tolkien
